Q2. Flux walking analysis:
A push-pull converter has switch S1 turning on for exactly 3µs each cycle, and S2 turning on for 3.2µs due to gate drive propagation delay mismatch.
(a) Net volt-second imbalance per cycle: ΔVt = V_in × (t_S1 − t_S2) = 24 × (3.0−3.2)×10⁻⁶
(b) This imbalance accumulates each cycle. After 100 cycles, what is the total net volt-second applied to the core?
(c) The magnetising inductance L_m = 50µH. The corresponding flux imbalance current after 100 cycles: ΔI_m = ΣΔVt / L_m. Find ΔI_m.
(d) If the core saturates at I_m_sat = 0.5A: how many cycles until saturation occurs?
(e) Current mode control checks peak current every cycle and limits S1 or S2 conduction to maintain equal peak currents. How does this prevent the accumulation calculated in (b)?
